newsitem.title: THAILAND: Thai interbank rate eases, baht steady late.
newsitem.headline: Thai interbank rate eases, baht steady late.

text.p: The Thai overnight interbank rate eased to 10.75-11.00 percent in late trade on Tuesday from 11.50 early as some dollar selling for baht help raise market liquidity, dealers said.
"Liquidity was higher today due to the selling of dollars for baht," said one dealer at a local bank.
Dealers said the liquidity was relatively tight this week due to the new bank reserve cycle and commercial banks' speculative dollar buying.
The baht was steady at 25.460-25.465 to the dollar late compared with 25.460-25.473 early, but there was some selling interest, dealers said.
"There was some selling of the dollar today as the dollar was falling in overseas markets," one currency dealer said.
Dollar/baht swap premiums were quoted at 9.00/10.00 satangs late against 10.25/10.75 early.
The Bank of Thailand fixed the dollar/baht mid-rate at 25.46 compared with 25.43 on Monday.
